{# DEPRECATED: maple.html.j2 is the legacy freeze-request template (pre-v0.14.8).
   It hardcodes "is currently held in" language without evidence_mode branching
   and MUST NOT be rendered directly — doing so would produce false claims on
   historical-receipt cases. brief.py explicitly refuses to fall back to this
   file (see brief.py generate_briefs error message). Preserved here only so
   that error message string "refusing to fall back to maple.html.j2" resolves
   to a real file path, aiding production debugging. Do NOT render this template.
   The active template is issuer_freeze_request.html.j2. #}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Freeze Request — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<header class="brief-header">
  <h1>Compliance Freeze Request</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Stolen Position Held in Identifiable Wallet — Time-Sensitive</p>
</header>

<dl class="meta-grid">
  <dt>To:</dt>          <dd>Maple Finance Compliance Team</dd>
  <dt>From:</dt>        <dd>Recupero (on behalf of victim)</dd>
  <dt>Date prepared:</dt><dd>{{ generated_at }}</dd>
  <dt>Case identifier:</dt><dd>{{ case_id }}</dd>
  <dt>Victim wallet:</dt><dd>{{ victim.wallet_address }}</dd>
  <dt>Stolen asset:</dt><dd>{{ asset.symbol }} ({{ asset.contract }})</dd>
</dl>

<div class="summary-box urgent">
  <p style="margin:0"><strong>Summary.</strong>
    {# v0.20.2 (audit-round-3 R3-3): roll up to multi-event total
       in the headline summary so V-CFI01-shape drains (6 × $600K =
       $3.6M) don't undersell the case. #}
    {% if asset.is_multi_event %}
    Between {{ theft_event.timestamp_human }} UTC and the following hours, the wallet of {{ victim.name }}
    ({{ victim.wallet_address }}) was drained of
    <strong>{{ asset.total_amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }}</strong>
    across {{ asset.theft_event_count }} transactions
    (cumulative initial value: <strong>USD {{ asset.total_usd_value_at_theft }}</strong>).
    {% else %}
    On {{ theft_event.timestamp_human }} UTC, the wallet of {{ victim.name }}
    ({{ victim.wallet_address }}) was drained of
    <strong>{{ asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }}</strong>
    (initial value: <strong>USD {{ asset.usd_value_at_theft }}</strong>).
    {% endif %}
    The stolen position was forwarded by the perpetrator within hours to wallet
    <span class="mono">{{ current_holder.address }}</span>,
    where on-chain records show
    <strong>it currently remains intact</strong>
    (last verified {{ verified_at }} UTC; no outbound transfers of this asset observed).
    We respectfully request that Maple Finance voluntarily freeze redemption rights on
    this specific position pending law enforcement engagement.
  </p>
</div>

<h2>1. Victim Identification</h2>
<dl class="meta-grid">
  <dt>Name:</dt>            <dd>{{ victim.name }}</dd>
  {% if victim.citizenship %}<dt>Citizenship:</dt><dd>{{ victim.citizenship }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.address %}<dt>Address:</dt><dd>{{ victim.address }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.email %}<dt>Email:</dt>      <dd>{{ victim.email }}</dd>{% endif %}
  {% if victim.phone %}<dt>Phone:</dt>      <dd>{{ victim.phone }}</dd>{% endif %}
  <dt>Wallet:</dt>          <dd>{{ victim.wallet_address }}</dd>
  {% if victim.legal_counsel %}
  <dt>Legal counsel:</dt><dd>{{ victim.legal_counsel }}{% if victim.legal_counsel_email %} &lt;{{ victim.legal_counsel_email }}&gt;{% endif %}</dd>
  {% endif %}
</dl>

{% if victim.incident_summary %}
<p>{{ victim.incident_summary }}</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>2. Theft Event</h2>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr><th>Date / time (UTC)</th><td class="mono">{{ theft_event.timestamp_human }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Block</th>             <td class="mono">{{ theft_event.block_number }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Transaction hash</th>  <td class="mono"><a href="{{ theft_event.explorer_url }}">{{ theft_event.tx_hash }}</a></td></tr>
  <tr><th>From (victim)</th>     <td class="mono victim-row">{{ theft_event.from_address }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>To (perpetrator)</th>  <td class="mono perp-row">{{ theft_event.to_address }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>Asset</th>             <td>{{ asset.symbol }} <span class="small">(contract: <span class="mono">{{ asset.contract }}</span>)</span></td></tr>
  {# v0.20.2 (audit-round-3 R3-3): aggregate across multi-event drains. #}
  <tr><th>Amount{% if asset.is_multi_event %} (total across {{ asset.theft_event_count }} events){% endif %}</th>            <td class="amount">{{ asset.total_amount_human if asset.is_multi_event else asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }}</td></tr>
  <tr><th>USD value at time of transaction</th><td class="amount">USD {{ asset.total_usd_value_at_theft if asset.is_multi_event else asset.usd_value_at_theft }}</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>3. Forwarding Chain (perpetrator's movements)</h2>
{% if hops %}
<p>After the theft, the funds moved through the following wallets controlled by the perpetrator:</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <tr>
    <th>Hop</th><th>Date (UTC)</th><th>Tx hash</th>
    <th>From</th><th>To</th><th>Amount</th>
  </tr>
  {% for hop in hops %}
  <tr>
    <td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
    <td class="mono">{{ hop.timestamp_human }}</td>
    <td class="mono"><a href="{{ hop.explorer_url }}">{{ hop.tx_hash[:14] }}…</a></td>
    <td class="mono perp-row">{{ hop.from_address }}</td>
    <td class="mono perp-row">{{ hop.to_address }}</td>
    <td class="amount">{{ hop.amount_human }} {{ hop.symbol }}</td>
  </tr>
  {% endfor %}
</table>
{% elif forwarding_observed %}
{# v0.20.1 (Jacob V-CFI01 residual #3): downstream destinations
   exist even though the linear hop chain is empty. #}
<p>
  The funds were forwarded from the initial receiving wallet
  through multiple downstream destinations rather than a single
  linear chain. Per-address current locations are documented in
  Section 4 below.
</p>
{% else %}
<p>No subsequent forwarding observed; the funds remain in the perpetrator's initial receiving wallet.</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>4. Current Location of Stolen Position</h2>
<div class="summary-box action">
  <p style="margin:0"><strong>The {{ asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }} position is currently held in:</strong></p>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:11pt; margin:0.5em 0;">{{ current_holder.address }}</p>
  <p style="margin:0">
    <a href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}">View on {{ primary_chain_explorer_name | default("the block explorer") }}</a>
    &nbsp;·&nbsp;
    <a href="{{ current_holder.explorer_url }}#tokentxns">Token transfer history</a>
  </p>
  <p style="margin:0.5em 0 0;">
    <strong>Last verified:</strong> {{ verified_at }} UTC.
    <strong>Outbound transfers of this asset observed:</strong> {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }}.
  </p>
</div>

<h2>5. Specific Request</h2>
<p>
  We request that Maple Finance compliance team take the following actions:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>
    <strong>Voluntarily freeze redemption rights</strong> on the
    {{ asset.amount_human }} {{ asset.symbol }} position currently held in
    <span class="mono">{{ current_holder.address }}</span>,
    pending engagement with law enforcement authorities representing the victim.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Confirm receipt of this request</strong> in writing, noting the date and time
    Maple Finance was placed on notice of the alleged theft.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Designate a point of contact</strong> for follow-up coordination with
    law enforcement. We anticipate a formal request from the relevant authorities to follow.
  </li>
</ol>
<p>
  We recognize Maple Finance is not a party to the underlying theft and are not asserting
  any wrongdoing on Maple's part. This request is made because Maple's protocol-level
  controls represent the most rapid available means of preventing further dissipation of
  the stolen funds while law enforcement procedures are initiated.
</p>

<h2>6. Independent Verification</h2>
<p>
  All facts in this brief are derived from public Ethereum mainnet data and are independently
  verifiable. Each transaction hash above links to its {{ primary_chain_explorer_name | default("block explorer") }} record. The on-chain state
  of <span class="mono">{{ current_holder.address }}</span> as of
  {{ verified_at }} UTC shows {{ outbound_count_of_stolen_asset }} outbound
  transfers of {{ asset.symbol }} from that wallet to date.
</p>
<p class="small">
  Data sources: {{ primary_chain_explorer_name | default("chain explorer") }} API ({{ primary_chain | default("Ethereum") }} transaction history),
  CoinGecko (historical USD valuation), Recupero label database
  (cross-case entity attribution).
</p>

<h2>7. Contact</h2>
<dl class="meta-grid">
  <dt>Investigator:</dt>  <dd>{{ investigator.name }}</dd>
  <dt>Organization:</dt>  <dd>{{ investigator.organization }}</dd>
  <dt>Email:</dt>         <dd>{{ investigator.email }}</dd>
  {% if investigator.phone %}<dt>Phone:</dt><dd>{{ investigator.phone }}</dd>{% endif %}
</dl>

<footer class="brief-footer">
  <p>
    Generated by Recupero v{{ software_version }} on {{ generated_at }} UTC.
    Case file: <span class="mono">{{ case_id }}</span>.
    Brief identifier: <span class="mono">{{ brief_id }}</span>.
  </p>
  <p>
    This document contains personally-identifiable information about the victim
    and is intended solely for the recipient's compliance and legal review.
  </p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
